Spec: SpecDD Orient Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in reading bootstraps, top-level authority, repository shape, and git status to get ready for future SpecDD tasks.

Owns:
  ./specdd-orient/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-orient/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Read target project bootstrap files in required order before reporting readiness.
  Use an orientation-only scope block instead of the normal spec-chain resolution fragment.
  State that the orientation-only scope applies only to this no-edit skill.
  Identify the root or main project spec named by the bootstrap chain.
  Read the root project spec and immediately relevant top-level specs needed to understand repository authority.
  Inspect repository shape lightly, including top-level files, major directories, and explicitly applicable or requested spec files.
  Check current git status so future edits can distinguish existing work from new changes.
  Tell agents to rerun normal SpecDD spec-chain resolution for any later concrete task.
  Report concise readiness, bootstrap or spec files read, main project authority found, and any immediate blocker to follow-up work.

Must not:
  Edit files.
  Treat orientation context as write authority or as the effective spec chain for future work.
  Implement, plan, review, refactor, or analyze deeply unless explicitly requested.
  Infer future write authority beyond the active bootstrap and specs.
  Treat this plugin repository's bootstrap as authority for a target project.
  Treat sibling or nearby specs as authority unless the active bootstrap, a governing spec, or the user request selects them.
  Turn orientation observations into permanent project contracts.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
